# CODEOWNERS for terraform-aws-iam
#
# This module manages IAM identities, trust policies, and account-level
# baselines (password policy, alias, Access Analyzer). Every change here
# directly affects who can assume what — Security has equity in every file,
# so the default rule routes review to both cloud-leads and security.
#
# Per Module-Repo Plan v1.3 §16 governance.

# Default: every change requires both teams to approve.
*                          @devotica-labs/cloud-leads @devotica-labs/security

# Trust / role definitions — Security is the primary owner here because
# changes to var.roles or data.aws_iam_policy_document.trust expand the
# blast radius of any compromised principal.
/main.tf                   @devotica-labs/security @devotica-labs/cloud-leads
/data.tf                   @devotica-labs/security @devotica-labs/cloud-leads
/variables.tf              @devotica-labs/security @devotica-labs/cloud-leads

# CI/CD pipelines have privileged OIDC role assumption — security is
# explicitly an owner so a config slip cannot bypass review.
/.github/                  @devotica-labs/cloud-leads @devotica-labs/security
/.github/workflows/        @devotica-labs/cloud-leads @devotica-labs/security
